Research Paper Intelligence System
Overview
Research Paper Intelligence System is an AI-powered research assistant that helps users discover, analyze, and understand machine learning research papers through semantic search and large language models.
The system indexes thousands of research papers by generating vector embeddings and storing them in a FAISS vector database. Instead of relying on keyword matching, it performs semantic retrieval to identify the most relevant papers for a given query.

Beyond retrieval, the system automatically summarizes papers, extracts important keywords, generates structured research profiles using large language models, and provides an intelligent interface for exploring academic literature.

Features
Semantic search using dense vector embeddings
Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) workflow
FAISS-based vector database for efficient similarity search
Research paper summarization using BART
Automatic keyword extraction using KeyBERT
AI-generated research paper profiles
Similarity-based paper ranking
LangChain tool integration
LLM-powered research assistant
Intelligent recommendation of related papers
